  <h3>Decision Guidance</h3>
  <p>Ask these questions:</p>
  <ol class="vf-list vf-list--ordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Is this page mostly informational? → SSG / ISR</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Need for fast content on slow networks? → SSG or SSR</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Low-end devices? → Avoid CSR</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Does failure matter (offline, unstable scenarios)? → Static + cached HTML</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Clear LRO Recommendations (Policy Style)</h3>

  <h4>Best for LRO</h4>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Static Site Generation (SSG)</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Incremental Static Regeneration (ISR)</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Progressive rendering</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Acceptable</h4>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">SSR with minimal hydration</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Hybrid with strict route rules</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Avoid</h4>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">CSR as default</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">SPA-only architectures for content pages</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Key Message for Developers</h3>
  <p>
    Rendering strategy is not just a framework choice.<br/>
    <strong>It is an inclusion decision.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>For LRO:</p>
  <ul class="vf-list vf-list--unordered">
    <li class="vf-list__item">Prefer static and server rendering</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Add JavaScript only when needed</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Design for failure</li>
    <li class="vf-list__item">Make content accessible first</li>
  </ul>

